<dl id="n54121i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54121i">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54121i"> 121(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ officials mild, <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54121i"><li>FW 57.05 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n54121i">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n54121i">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54121i">MS BL 47476a-174</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:369 <a name="cd10" href="../../FF/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n54121i">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;My mother&apos;s brother, and my husband were killed here by a ferocious tiger;&rdquo; she said, &ldquo;and now my son has met the same fate.&rdquo; <p>&ldquo;Why do you not move away from such a dangerous neighborhood?&rdquo; inquired the disciple.</p> <p>&ldquo;But <mark>the officials here are not oppressive</mark>,&rdquo; the woman explained&rsquo;</p> <p>Master Kung was told of the incident and said to his discipes:</p> <p>&ldquo;You hear that, my children! An oppressive official is more to be feared than a dangerous tiger.&rdquo;</p> <small> Carl Crow, <a name="CCMK" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CCMK"><cite title="source">Master Kung. The Story of Confucius</cite></a> (Sep 1937) 123</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
